des:
Enhance your Smart Home experience with Amazon Alexa and Victure's products.

If you own an Alexa Echo Show, you can ask Alexa Echo Show to display the live view from your Victure Cam.

Follow the steps here to connect your Victure account to Amazon Alexa:
1. Download the "Victure" app from the app store;
2. Register a Victure account to add your devices;
3. Configure your devices and name the devices;
4. Download the "Amazon Alexa" app from the app store;
5. Configure Alexa Echo Show in the "Amazon Alexa" app;
6. Search for "Victure" from the skills category in the "Amazon Alexa" app;
7. Enable "Victure" skill, and you'll be navigated to Victure's login page;
8. Log into your Victure account to finish.

Once the "Victure" Skill is enabled, simply ask Alexa to control your Victure devices by their names. For example:
“Alexa, show (name of device)"
“Alexa, stop"

Currently this skill supports:
Victure Cam PC420

If you experience any problems while using this skill, please contact us at support@govicture.com
